com.m87.sdk
Class ProximityManager

java.lang.Object
  com.m87.sdk.ProximityManager

public class ProximityManager
extends java.lang.Object

This class implements a wrapper to M87 Proximity SDK for apps. Applications can use the SDK to discover proximate devices that are one or more hops away. Future releases of the SDK will allow apps to exchange short messages and rich media with proximate devices that are one or more hops away.

M87 Proximity SDK uses a publish/subscribe paradigm, wherein a publisher transmits expressions and a subscriber receives expressions. Expressions can be used by applications to broadcast their needs/services. See LTE-Direct expressions for more details.

An app should instantiate a single ProximityManager object in it's main activity. ProximityManager will handle converting all asynchronous events from the SDK to the application's main looper, allowing any callback processing to run in the app's thread context.

The app must pass in an implementation of the ProximityManager.Callbacks interface to receive events from the SDK.

subscribe

public int subscribe(int transactionId,
                     java.lang.String expression,
                     int range)
Subscribes to M87 Proximity SDK

Enables the application to subscribe for expressions from proximate devices. The onSubscribe callback provides the status asynchronously. The onMatch callback provides expressions from proximate devices that match the expression subscribed by the app.

Parameters:
transactionId - transaction ID
expression - expression string
range - the range of the subscription request
Returns:
0 if the request was submitted successfully

cancelSubscribe

public int cancelSubscribe(int transactionId,
                           java.lang.String expression)
Cancels subscription to M87 Proximity SDK

Once subscription is canceled, the application will not receive events corresponding to proximate devices. The app must subscribe again to receive these events. The onCancelSubscribe callback provides the status asynchronously.

Parameters:
transactionId - transaction ID
expression - expression string
Returns:
0 if the request was submitted successfully
